install vim windows and call vim windows from cygwin to avoid syntax/installation issues
for vim windows:
.vimrc ==> c/programfiles/Vim/_vimrc
~/.vim/colors ==> c/programfiles/Vim/vimfiles/colors  

setup Vim profile at ~./vimrc
for syntax highlighting, need to download 
most updated python.vim and put into 
/usr/share/vim/vim73/syntax/python.vim
need to open with administrator rights and chg for gvim to load vimrc as well

    " set fileformat (no 's' for single file use) =unix or =dos
    set fileformats=dos
    " syntax highlighting
    syntax on
    " tab width = 4 spaces
    set tabstop=4
    " indent width = 4
    set shiftwidth=4
    "indent rounded to next full shift width
    set shiftround
    " expand tabs to spaces
    set expandtab
    "auto-indent code blocks
    set autoindent
    " always enable status line
    set laststatus=2
    " change status line color based on mode
    if version >= 700
    au InsertEnter * hi StatusLine term=reverse ctermbg=5 gui=undercurl guisp=Magenta
    au InsertLeave * hi StatusLine term=reverse ctermfg=0 ctermbg=2 gui=bold,reverse
    endif
    "show line numbers
    set number
    "show row and column
    set ruler
    "remaps ; to : for easier commands
    nnoremap ; ::yntax on


search and replace \ for /
:s/\\/\//g
:s/__/__/g
the exit character is \ 

installing pathogen
- git clone from https://github.com/tpope/vim-pathogen.git
- copy into programfiles/vim/vimfiles/autoload/pathogen.vim
installing plugins
- download/git clone to desktop
- copy into programfiles/vim/vimfiles/bundle/
- will be bundle/plugin_folder/autoload, bundle/plugin_folder/colors etc
- call plugins:
    - NERDTree
    - 
